((=-

    Colombia FX-vol notebooks — nbconvert LaTeX template.

    This template is intentionally one-line thin: it extends nbconvert's
    bundled ``latex/index.tex.j2`` (the stock "article" output) and adds
    NO Jinja overrides. All cell-hiding behavior is delegated to
    ``TagRemovePreprocessor`` wired up in the sibling
    ``jupyter_nbconvert_config.py``. That preprocessor strips the source
    of any code cell tagged ``remove-input`` before the notebook ever
    reaches the template layer, so the template only has to render what
    the default article template renders.

    Rationale for keeping this file minimal (vs. a Jinja ``block
    input_group`` override):
      * The TagRemovePreprocessor path is the officially documented one
        (nbconvert docs: "Removing cells from notebooks" page).
      * A Jinja override of ``input_group`` would couple us to the exact
        block names in nbconvert's latex templates, which shift between
        minor releases of the package.
      * Fewer moving parts → fewer ways for a future developer to
        accidentally leak boilerplate imports into the PDF.

    Do not delete the ``latex`` prefix on the extends path below: nbconvert
    disambiguates between markdown/latex/html/rst variants of
    ``index.tex.j2`` by that prefix when it builds the Jinja search path.

-=))
((*- extends 'latex/index.tex.j2' -*))
